<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,152,332]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
From all points of view they fit the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thor, 1899" authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1899" box="[822,1101,152,178]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellichi">
<emphasis box="[822,952,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. hellichi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thor" box="[962,1101,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="33" refString="Thor, S. (1899) Tredie bidrag til kundskaben om Norges Hydrachnider. - &quot; Norske Hydrachnider &quot; III. Archiv for Mathematik og Naturvidenskab, 21, 1 - 64." type="journal article" year="1899">
Thor, 
<number box="[1037,1101,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1899.0">1899</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a species synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad" box="[151,356,190,216]" pageId="14" pageNumber="32" refString="Lundblad, C. O. (1962) Die Hydracarinen Schwedens. II. Arkiv for Zoologi 14 (2), 1 - 635." type="journal article" year="1962">
Lundblad (
<number box="[284,347,190,216]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1962.0">1962</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName box="[427,531,191,216]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[427,531,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, Lundblad demonstrated that specimens with an elongated frontal shield (as described for 
<taxonomicName box="[434,558,229,254]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hellichi">
<emphasis box="[434,558,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. hellichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) could coexist with specimens bearing a more compact, 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1295,229,254]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[1231,1295,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like frontal shield, and that within a single population intermediate character states could bridge the gap between the two extremes. Thus, 
<taxonomicName box="[344,476,306,331]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipes">
<emphasis box="[344,476,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. spinipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[755,854,306,331]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[755,854,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
